cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.SDQ 

The paper proposes a new method for speaker diarization using deep learning architecture, specifically a recurrent convolutional neural network. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Speech and Signal Processing (cs.SD), Computation and Language (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Sound and Music Computing (cs.SDQ). However, given that the focus is on speaker diarization, cs.SD is the most likely category. The use of deep learning and neural networks also suggests that cs.CL and cs.LG are likely categories. The potential applications in social and information networks could also make cs.SI a relevant category. Finally, the focus on audio processing could make cs.SDQ a possible category as well.
